# Python coding standards

> Derived from the current codebase. Apply to all new and changed Python code.

## Toolchain

- Python **3.12+**, managed with **uv workspace**
- **Ruff**: line length 100, rules E / F / I / UP
- **mypy strict** ‚Äî every public function must be fully typed
- **pytest + pytest-asyncio** (`asyncio_mode = auto`)
- Do not merge if lint or type checks fail

## Monorepo layout

- **src layout**: `packages/<name>/src/<name>/`
- **apps/api** ‚Äî HTTP entrypoints, deps, request/response schemas
- **packages/core** ‚Äî config, auth, exceptions, LLM clients, shared utils
- **packages/db** ‚Äî ORM models, Alembic migrations, service functions
- **packages/agents** ‚Äî orchestration, streaming, memory, prompt loading
- **packages/tools** ‚Äî individual agent tools
- Packages **must not** import from apps
- Cross-package imports use package names (`db`, `core`, `agents`‚Ä¶), not relative paths across workspace boundaries

## Layering

One job per layer ‚Äî do not absorb concerns from another layer.

| Layer | Does | Does not |
|-------|------|----------|
| Routes | validate HTTP, auth, call services, map schemas | SQL, business rules, agent logic |
| Services | DB query/mutation, scope `user_id` | raise HTTPException |
| Core | infra, domain exceptions (`code` + `message`) | feature orchestration |
| Agents | LLM turns, tools, streaming events | HTTP |
| Tools | one clear action, return string to loop | ‚Äî |

- Place code at the lowest layer that can fully own the feature
- Extend existing patterns ‚Äî no new abstraction used in only one place

## Code style

- `from __future__ import annotations` in new modules
- **async def** for all I/O (DB, HTTP, LLM, filesystem)
- **Function-first** for stateless logic
- **Dataclass / Pydantic** for data shapes
- **Class** only for: ORM models, Settings, runtime context, exception hierarchies
- Private helpers: `_` prefix
- Optional filters after required args ‚Üí **keyword-only** (`*`)
- Modern types: `str | None`, `list[str]`, `Literal` ‚Äî no `Optional`, `List`
- Import order: stdlib ‚Üí third-party ‚Üí local
- Lazy import inside functions ‚Äî only to break circular dependencies between packages
- Limits, timeouts, file names, protocol markers ‚Üí **constants module**
- Avoid magic numbers and repeated string literals in business logic

## Config & secrets

- Env vars only via **Settings** (pydantic-settings)
- New variables ‚Üí document in `.env.example`
- Never commit or embed: secrets, tokens, API keys, production URLs
- Feature flags and provider selection ‚Üí config, not scattered conditionals

## Error handling

- Domain errors ‚Üí typed exceptions with stable `code` + `message`
- HTTP layer maps exceptions to status codes via registered handlers
- Routes raise HTTP only for transport concerns (e.g. service returns `None` ‚Üí 404)
- Re-raise known errors; wrap with `from e` preserved
- No bare `except` or silent swallowing

## Database

- Models ‚Üí schema; services ‚Üí all queries and mutations
- Insert: `flush` + `refresh` for generated fields
- Update: whitelist allowed columns ‚Äî no arbitrary kwargs
- Authorization: filter `user_id` in services, not only in routes
- Schema changes ‚Üí Alembic migration in `packages/db`

## Logging

- Agents/runtime ‚Üí **structlog**
- Elsewhere ‚Üí standard logging
- Log: ids, duration, phase, error codes
- Do not log: full LLM prompts, user message bodies, PII

## Testing

- API tests: beside `apps/api`, async HTTP client, shared auth helpers
- Package tests: inside each package
- Assert: behavior, HTTP status, data shape
- Do not assert: internal call order, exact marketing copy, LLM prose
- Use fixtures instead of copy-paste setup

## Change discipline

- Smallest correct diff for the requirement
- Match naming, structure, and patterns of the file being edited
- No unrelated refactors in the same PR
- No helpers, base classes, or indirection used only once
- Comments only for business rules or protocol constraints ‚Äî do not narrate code

## No hardcode

- Business rules, tunable thresholds, provider endpoints, env paths ‚Üí config or named constants
- User-visible text in the API layer ‚Üí stable messages on exception classes
- No fixed multi-line strings for dynamic or contextual responses

## No hard prompt / agent copy

- Assistant behavior ‚Üí **prompt MD** in `packages/agents/prompts/`
- Python (`agents`, `tools`) = plumbing: load prompts, advance phases, spawn, stream model output, persist
- `user_instructions` = short pointer to a workflow step ‚Äî do not paraphrase message body
- Automatic pipeline that needs user acknowledgment ‚Üí add an orchestrator LLM turn
- Details: `agent-no-hardcode.mdc`; prompt conventions: `agent-prompts.mdc`

## Review checklist

- [ ] Correct layer boundaries
- [ ] No secrets, no duplicated prompt text
- [ ] No new canned assistant messages
- [ ] Types and async match surrounding code
- [ ] Services enforce ownership (`user_id`)
- [ ] Tests cover behavior, not LLM wording
